<! screenshot !>
<p class="p1"><a href="screenshots.html"><img src="graphics/beanscrn.jpg" BORDER="0.0" align="right" alt="Screenshot of Bean"></a></p>

<! description of Bean !>
<p class="p1" align="justify" >Bean is a <b>small, easy-to-use</b> word processor (or more precisely, a rich text editor), designed to make writing convenient, efficient and comfortable. Bean is <b>Open Source</b>, <b>fully Cocoa</b>, and is available <b>free of charge</b>! MS Word, OpenOffice, etc. try to be all things to all people. But sometimes you just want the right tool for the job. That is Bean&#39;s niche.</p>
<p class="p2"><br></p>

<p class="p1">Some <a href="screenshots.html">screenshots</a>.</p>
<br>

<! Origins of Bean !>
<p class="p1">Read about the origins of Bean <a href="Essay.html">here</a>.</p>
<p class="p2"><br></p>

<! Bean is not Word !>
<p class="p1" align="justify" >Bean is <b>not</b> a replacement for MS Word. It doesn&#39;t do footnotes or use stylesheets and is only <a href="Word97.html">partially compatible</a> with Word&#39;s file formats.</p>
<br>

